quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
5,109,"The Day {1} when Allah will gather together the Messengers {2} and say: 'What answer were you given?' They will reply: 'We have no real knowledge of it. {3} You alone fully know all that lies beyond the reach of human perception.",footnotes:1:This refers to the Day of Judgement.The reference here is to the response of the world to the call of the Prophets.This reply indicates that the Prophets would say that their knowledge was confined to that limited
5,110,"Imagine, then,"when Allah will say: {1} 'Jesus", son of Mary, recall My favour upon you and your mother, and when I strengthened you with the spirit of holiness so that you talked to men in the cradle and also when you became of age; and when I taught you the Book and Wisdom, and the Torah and the Gospel; and when, by My leave, you fashioned from clay the likeness of a bird and you breathed into it, and by My leave it became a bird; you healed, by My leave, the blind from birth and the leprous; and when, by My leave, you caused the dead to come to life. 2 And recall when I restrained the Israelites from you when you came to them with clear proofs whereupon those of them who disbelieved said: "This is nothing but clear magic.",footnotes:1:The initial question would be addressed to all Prophets as such. Then each of them would be called upon to bear witness separately
5,111,"And recall when I revealed to the disciples to believe in Me and in My Mes-senger, they said: "We do believe, and we bear witness that we indeed are the ones who submit to Allah"<sup foot_note="177843">1</sup>",footnotes:177843:Jesus is being told that the faith of the disciples in him was also the result of God's grace and succour, for he, himself, did not have the power to produce even one man of faith in that land of disbelief. It is also made clear that the true religion of the disciples of Jesus was Islam.
5,112,"Also recall when the disciples asked Jesus, {1} son of Mary: 'Jesus, son of Mary, has your Lord the power to send down to us a repast from the heaven?' There- upon Jesus said: 'Fear Allah if you do indeed have faith.'",footnotes:1:Since the disciples have been mentioned here
5,113,"They said: 'We desire to partake of it that our hearts be satisfied and we know that you did speak the truth to us, and that we are its witnesses.'"
